Pre-Requirements:
  - Wiring Pi
    http://wiringpi.com/


Build How To

  1. Run configure
     $ ./configure --with-wiring-pi=/path/to/wiringpi/headers

  2. Run make
     $ make

  3. Install
     $ su -
     # make install


Uninstall How To

  1. Run make
     $ su -
     # make uninstall


NOTES:
  ToyHack libraries will be installed to /usr/local/lib by default.
  However, some Linux Distros does not set /usr/local/lib to library path.
  You have to check library path and to set LD_LIBRARY_PATH.

